{
  "texts": [
    "The classification accuracy ranged from 80 to 93%.",
    "Waheed et al. (2020) employed an optimized DenseNet model for three corn leaf disease detection and classification.",
    "The total trainable parameters were 77,612.",
    "The optimized DensNet classification accuracy was compared with the VGGNet, XceptionNet, Efficient-Net, and NASNet.",
    "The DL models were competent on the 12,332 images dataset."
  ]
